reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works great for Apple Carplay.
reviews.reviewText: My 2023 Honda Ridgeline RTL-E doesn't have wireless Apple Carplay, so I use this cord to connect my iPhone 14 to the designated APC input on my dash. So far, both the APC and the charging functions are working great. The coiled cord is very convenient for in-vehicle use -- avoids having to deal with excessive length, while allowing me to pick up the phone while connected when necessary. The cord and connectors appear to be well-made. Too early to determine durability.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect Decluttering Solution
reviews.reviewText: I always plug in my phone in the car so I have Apple Play working in case I need easy access to things while I am driving. But I HATED having long cords that would get stepped on and damaged and tangled within the center console of my car. This fixed that problem so easily. The coils stretch easily and limit the clutter of my car! The ends of the cord seem sturdy and the cord has good weight to it. I love that it came with 2 cords just in case, price point is very worth it!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Seems to be a quality product at a reasonable price, plus you get 2 of them!
reviews.reviewText: Honest review of Coiled Lightning Cable, iPhone Charger Cable 3FT for Car, 2 Pack [Apple MFi Certified] 3 Feet Lightning Cord Compatible with iPhone14/13/12/11 Pro Max/XS MAX/XR/XS/X/8/7/Plus/6S iPad/iPod- Black @ $15.69 at time of order.The way that I had to mount my phone mount in my vehicle left me wanting a better charger cable than what I had on hand. The one I had was too long really, and I had it coiled up and, in the way, – way too bulky as well. This seemed to be a great solution.I felt that this was a good value getting 2 coiled cables at this price. They seem sturdy and work fine with my iPhone 14 Pro. I tested both of them. They stretch out long enough but aren’t in the way when not plugged in. They’re easy to store as well. There’s also a code to scan with your phone’s camera that takes you to a Facebook Messenger chat to request an upgraded 2-year warranty.I was fortunate that it did not affect me, but the only thing I did not like was that to use Apple CarPlay, it takes a little extra work in some cases as the instructions imply. This requires going into settings in your phone to get these cables to work in some cases. However, it worked just fine with the USB plug in my 2016 F150. In this case, it is an updated USB that I purchased from Ford because 2017 is when they started making USB plugins compatible with CarPlay, so I don’t know if this had anything to do with it or not. My other vehicle is older and has no USB outlets at all. In it, I had to use a USB cigarette lighter plug and it worked just fine with that too.Hopefully this helps someone decide on this product.5 stars.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars The cables have both stopped working just outside the return window.
reviews.reviewText: I don’t blame the cable I blame apple I have a Samsung phone with usb c port and it’s almost 3 years old with the original cable and everything still works. I use the lightning cable in my car for apple car play to get better quality while listening to music. I buy up to 5 cables a year because they keep disconnecting. Apples lightning cable is usb 2.0 that standard is 23 years old!!! And if I want a apple phone with usb c I need to pay $1000-1500.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works with CarPlay & stretchy!
reviews.reviewText: Standard cords were just too long. They would get caught on my bags, tangled around stuff, and constant snagging ruined my car cord over time. And then I found this! Lifesaving cord, no more getting tangled in and around the dash, coils up nicely but has enough stretch to reach my phone propped in a vent pop socket stand! I have all black interior so it blends in and sits nicely when not in use. Hoping it lasts bc I love!

reviews.reviewText: Cable is built solid with good apparent quality. I rated 3 stars as at only one month worth of use it would not establish a solid connection with my iPhone. I would have to disconnect and reconnect multiple times. I have tested other cables confirming that my iPhone is not the issue.

Good quality cable along with nicely sealed ends plated in red. I bought them because they match the interior of my car black and red. I was a bit surprised to see this nice of quality at this price point. I think having the coil helps keep the wire in place better. I would recommend this one. Oh and you get two !!
